Election Day.

What are we looking for?

At Raybeam, we pride ourselves on our pragmatic, engineering approach to making data work for the business.

About the Role
The ideal candidate for this role will have a passion for a detail oriented, statistical approach to scientific data analysis. You will analyze biosignals recorded by new graphene based electronics coupled to active biological components. Analysis will be done using a variety of platforms such as Prism and Python Notebooks. You will coordinate with our Software Development Team to integrate successful new analysis approaches into our internally developed analysis software. The candidate will report to the Measurement Group Leader.
Responsibilities, but not limited to:
· Collaborate closely with bench scientists to perform statistical evaluation of experiment results
· Create reports and presentations summarizing data and analysis for both internal and partner driven projects

Each of our clients is unique. They have their own workflows and very specific data needs. Our endless selection of datasets, covering all asset types, with multiple delivery technologies and flexible scheduling means our clients are able to get exactly the data they need, when they need it, in the format they prefer. Without us, they simply cannot operate. Making the right decisions for our customers and services with such varying and complex consumption is a challenge. Extracting intelligence from our datasets is key to our success and that is where you come in.

What is the role?

The Business Intelligence team drives new business and organic growth in the Enterprise Data department through providing actionable insights to key decision makers. Whether we are working on the design of products and commercial strategies or uncovering sales opportunities through data analysis, technology, collaboration and understanding of our customers is at the heart of everything we do.

We work closely with both regional and global teams across stakeholder groups such as Sales, CFO Office, Global & Regional Department Heads, Business and Product Development, Global Data, Operational Support and other verticals across the firm. In order to achieve our goals and deliver results we extensively leverage technology for data warehousing, analysis and visualization (Qliksense, IBM Cognos, Tableau, Excel PowerPivot, VBA, SQL, Python, R).

LDSS is looking for a data analyst for one of our long time DoD clients. The data team is mining data from legacy logistics systems and migrating that data to an Air Force platform/Cloud. As they mine the data, they are performing analysis and cleansing as part of the migration process. There is a large number of legacy systems and a lot of data that needs to eventually be migrated to the AF platform and using Appian will improve this process.

About us
LDSS is a Woman-Owned Small Business headquartered in Dayton, Ohio. We have built a strong reputation with our customers as a premier provider of highly-qualified and capable professionals delivering Leading and Dynamic Services and Solutions!
LDSS is looking for a data analyst for one of our long time DoD clients. The data team is mining data from legacy logistics systems and migrating that data to an Air Force platform/Cloud. As they mine the data, they are performing analysis and cleansing as part of the migration process. LDSS is looking for a data analyst for one of our long time DoD clients. The data team is mining data from legacy logistics systems and migrating that data to an Air Force platform/Cloud. As they mine the data, they are performing analysis and cleansing as part of the migration process.
